                <h2>Micro-Drip vs. SDI for Citrus</h2>
                <p>Both micro-emitter and subsurface drip systems perform well in citrus. The right choice depends on your rootstock, soil, and operational priorities:</p>
                <ul class="check-list" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <li><strong>Micro-drip:</strong> Lower upfront cost, easier to inspect, ideal for shallow-rooted systems on trifoliate rootstocks</li>
                    <li><strong>SDI:</strong> Premium long-term solution for growers with established orchards on deeper rootstocks</li>
                    <li>Both deliver equivalent water savings and fruit quality benefits</li>
                    <li>DripSmart will help you model the 10-year economics of each option</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:28px;display:inline-block;">Request a System Comparison</a>
